questions.article: The cost to rent a bus from Company X is $850 for the first 2 hours and an additional $30 per hour for each hour after the first 2 hours. If the total cost to rent the bus from Company X for t hours, where t > 2, is $1,030, which equation represents this situation?

options.name: A
options.content: 850(t−2)+30t=1,030 ​​​​​​​

options.name: B
options.content: 850(2t)+30t=1,030 ​​​​​​​

options.name: C
options.content: 850+30(t−2)=1,030 ​​​​​​​

options.name: D
options.content: 850+30(2t)=1,030 ​​​​​​​

questions.correct: 850+30(t−2)=1,030 ​​​​​​​

questions.article: A machine fills bags with approximately 29 ounces of walnuts. To test the accuracy of the filling process, 169 bags of walnuts were selected at random and weighed. Based on the sample, it is estimated that the average weight of all bags of walnuts filled by the machine in an 8-hour period is 28,88 ounces, with an associated margin of error of 0.13 ounce. Which of the following is the best interpretation of this estimate?

options.name: A
options.content: Plausible values for the average weight of all bags of walnuts filled by the machine are between 28.75 ounces and 29,01 ounces.

options.name: B
options.content: Plausible values for the average weight of all bags of walnuts filled by the machine are less than 28,75 ounces or greater than 29.0l ounces.

options.name: C
options.content: The average weight of all bags of walnuts filled by the machine is less than 28.99 ounces.

options.name: D
options.content: The average weight of all bags of walnuts filled by the machine is greater than 28.99 ounces.

questions.correct: Plausible values for the average weight of all bags of walnuts filled by the machine are between 28.75 ounces and 29,01 ounces.

The function f(x)= 242(1.040)x models the value, in dollars, of a certain bank account from 1953 through 1968, where x is the number of years after the end of 1953. Which of the following is the best interpretation of “f(5) is approximately equal to 294” in this context?

options.name: A
options.content: The value of the bank account is estimated to be approximately 5 dollars greater at the end of 1958 than at the end of 1953.

options.name: B
options.content: The value of the bank account is estimated to be approximately 294 dollars at the end of 1958.

options.name: C
options.content: The value, in dollars, of the bank account is estimated to be approximately 5times greater at the end of 1958 than at the end of 1953.

options.name: D
options.content: The value of the bank account is estimated to increase by approximately 294 dollars every 5 years between the end of 1953 and the end of 1968.

questions.correct: The value of the bank account is estimated to be approximately 294 dollars at the end of 1958.
